            "editorial-title": "LAYOUT 2 CABINS"
          }
        },
        "text_area_gmtHcx": {
          "type": "text-area",
          "settings": {
            "editor-text": "Below deck, every detail is designed to ensure the highest level of comfort worthy of a true Long Cruise yacht. The large hull windows give the interiors a bright and airy atmosphere. The attention to detail and the well-planned layout create the perfect setting for extended cruising. On the starboard side, the saloon features a three-seater sofa, with the central seat convertible into a chart table. The galley is fully equipped to provide maximum comfort and generous storage space.\n\nThe owner’s cabin has been designed to offer optimal storage capacity, with three lockers, two drawers under the bed, shelves and bookcases along the sides, and a large wardrobe.\n\nThe Grand Soleil 42 Long Cruise offers two interior layouts to suit different needs on board. In the two-cabin version (opt.) shown here, the starboard aft cabin is fitted with two single V-shaped berths. In the 2-cabin layout, the galley is more spacious and offers increased storage capacity, thanks to the absence of the second aft cabin featured in the 3-cabin configuration.",
            "editorial-label": "",
            "editorial-url": ""
          }
        },
